void gtrack_moduleAllocate ( GtrackModuleInstance *  inst,
GTRACK_measurementPoint *  point,
uint16_t  num 
)

Description
This is a MODULE level allocation function. The function is called by external step function to allocate new targets for the non-associated measurement points

Parameters
[in]instPointer to GTRACK module instance
[in]pointPointer to an array of input measurments. Each measurement has range/angle/radial velocity information
[in]numNumber of input measurements
Return values
None

void gtrack_moduleReport ( GtrackModuleInstance *  inst,
GTRACK_targetDesc *  t,
uint16_t *  tNum 
)

Description
This is a MODULE level report function. The function is called by external step function to obtain unit level data

Parameters
[in]instPointer to GTRACK module instance
[out]tPointer to an array of GTRACK_targetDesc. This function populates the descritions for each of the tracked target
[out]tNumPointer to a uint16_t value. Function returns a number of populated target descriptos
Return values
None
void gtrack_moduleUpdate ( GtrackModuleInstance *  inst,
GTRACK_measurementPoint *  point,
GTRACK_measurement_vector *  var,
uint16_t  num 
)

Description
This is a MODULE level update function. The function is called by external step function to perform unit level kalman filter updates

Parameters
[in]instPointer to GTRACK module instance
[in]pointPointer to an array of input measurments. Each measurement has range/angle/radial velocity information
[in]varPointer to an array of input measurment variances. Set to NULL if variances are unknown
[in]numNumber of input measurements
Return values
None
